article.headline: Houston Baptist 65, Texas-Pan American 58
article.story: HOUSTON -- Joe Latas had 18 points and 10 rebounds, and Terry Bembry and Anthony Hill added 14 points each to lead Houston Baptist to a 65-58 victory against Texas-Pan American on Saturday night. Tyler Russell had 10 points for the Huskies (10-19, 3-7 Great West), who will be the No. 5 seed at next week's conference tournament. The opponent, the No. 4 seed, is to be determined. The seedings of Texas-Pan American (11-20, 5-5) and NJIT will not be finalized until Sunday. The schools tied for third in the Great West, with the determination of the Nos. 3 and 4 seeds going to the third tiebreaker, which is RPI. Jared Maree had 18 points for the Broncs, who were without leading scorer Brandon Provost, who suffered an undisclosed injury in practice on Friday. A 14-2 run midway through the second half gave the Huskies a 58-53 cushion. They never relinquished that lead.
